Dominik Ridjic on 2016-07-19 19:26:04.580000 wrote (thread 578e62ac00a388401f935c1a52301d9b):

 I've discovered a big issue, that both causes problems with DataForm search for users and for domains.
Here's an example query & result for user search:

query:
<iq to='search.sipwise.com' id='hUU0q-90' type='set'><query xmlns='jabber:iq:search'><x xmlns='jabber:x:data' type='submit'><field var='FORM_TYPE' type='hidden'><value>jabber:iq:search</value></field><field var='e164' type='text-single'><value>4313012039</value></field></x></query></iq>

result:
<iq id='hUU0q-90' type='result' to='sparrowlabs@sipwise.com/a62e1c69-c6c5-4a11-8e65-66b7228ee630' from='search.sipwise.com'><query xmlns='jabber:iq:search'><item jid='dboghici@sipwise.com'/></query></iq>

The problem here is that while my query is a DataForm query, the response is not! It doesn't use DataForms.

In the specification of the search XEP you'll see that when you use DataForms in the query, the response should be a DataForm with jabber:x:data, if you don't then the result should not use DataForms.

https://xmpp.org/extensions/xep-0055.html#extensibility

My problem is that my client library closely follows that specification, so when it then receives a non DataForm answer it can't parse the result (although I see that I got the response from the server)

So we would need the following change:

If I send a query with a DataForm, please return a DataForm response
If I send the old format, please return in the old format.

Dominik
